    "created_at": "2013-11-21T18:31:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-11-21T18:32:26Z",
    "body": "And here is the code I was trying to use in Atom with the `--allow-http-screen-capture` flag set in [AtomApplication](https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/src/browser/atom-application.coffee#L110)\n\n``` coffeescript\noptions = video:\n  mandatory:\n    chromeMediaSource: 'screen'\n\nerror = (e) -> console.log(\"getUserMedia error: \", e)\nsuccess = (stream) =>\n  video = document.querySelector(\"video\")\n  video.src = window.URL.createObjectURL(stream)\n  video.play()\nnavigator.webkitGetUserMedia options, success, error\n```\n"
  },
